WEBVTT

00:01.282 --> 00:19.690
So Jesus called the crowds, and they gathered with his disciples, and he said to them, if anyone would come after me, let him deny himself and take up his cross and follow me.

00:22.193 --> 00:30.546
Because whoever would save his life is going to lose it, and whoever

00:30.658 --> 00:35.165
loses his life from my sake and the gospels, we'll save it.

00:37.608 --> 00:44.719
Because what is a prophet a man if he gains the whole world and forfeits his life?

00:46.261 --> 00:50.267
Because what can a man give in exchange for his life?

00:51.629 --> 01:00.242
Because everyone who's ashamed of me and my words and this adulterous and sinful generation

01:01.794 --> 01:08.484
I'm going to be ashamed of him when I come in the glory of my father and the holy angels.

01:13.511 --> 01:29.714
So if you want to follow Jesus, then you deny yourself and you take up your cross and you get behind him because, because, because, because.

01:33.762 --> 01:44.114
I'm going to linger here at the surface level of grammar and words for just a moment to make two points.

01:45.475 --> 02:02.354
First, if any graduates can read Mark 834 to 38 and not see the four layers of argumentation that Jesus gives for following him, then

02:03.842 --> 02:06.224
In your case, we have failed.

02:08.947 --> 02:10.108
Because that's what we do here.

02:13.831 --> 02:22.300
We have linked arms to learn how to see us, what we do.

02:24.081 --> 02:29.787
We teach people to see what's there, really there.

02:32.489 --> 02:33.330
So that's the first point.

02:35.586 --> 02:43.516
Second point, we don't just teach people how to see, we teach them how to see through.

02:43.536 --> 02:53.610
I think who cares about words, words, words, words, grammar, grammar, grammar, grammar.

02:53.790 --> 02:54.431
Who cares?

02:55.132 --> 02:57.955
Well, God must care because that's what he gave us.

02:59.417 --> 03:03.122
But not really, not ultimately, I mean, who cares?

03:05.570 --> 03:15.462
If we don't see through to reality, so that's what we do here.

03:15.562 --> 03:26.636
We train each other, we link arms to learn how to see what's there and how to see through to reality.

03:27.738 --> 03:34.386
Ultimately, the greatest reality that you've been hearing from these students, God.

03:38.690 --> 03:41.094
Almost all my earthly life is behind me.

03:41.915 --> 03:42.896
It's an awesome thought.

03:45.640 --> 03:46.842
Totally unchangeable.

03:49.406 --> 03:50.107
Awesome thought.

03:52.631 --> 03:58.099
And I hope to live the rest of it, it won't be big, just little.

03:59.341 --> 04:03.647
The little that's left with all the might that God gives me.

04:06.211 --> 04:08.434
But as I look back,

04:10.082 --> 04:24.558
It has struck me increasingly clearly that for 50 years, almost all my time has been spent trying to see what's there and say it.

04:27.081 --> 04:32.988
Understand it, evaluate it, feel it, apply it, say it.

04:33.969 --> 04:35.090
That's all I do.

04:37.762 --> 04:48.877
That's what we want, we want those habits of mind and heart to carry you all the way to see through to reality.

04:48.957 --> 05:04.478
So let me take the rest of my few minutes to take those four verses and just zero in mainly on the fourth layer, one at the bottom of the argument for why to follow Jesus.

05:05.699 --> 05:07.602
So here's my paraphrase.

05:07.970 --> 05:12.997
unpacking each of the four layers of argumentation.

05:13.258 --> 05:14.560
So take up your cross.

05:17.584 --> 05:18.686
Deny yourself.

05:19.226 --> 05:33.587
Follow me because preferring comfort over cross bearing will destroy you and preferring Christ over life will save you.

05:34.308 --> 05:35.570
That's argument number one.

05:36.322 --> 05:37.303
Why is that?

05:37.403 --> 05:40.526
Because I think the arguments basically argue for the one just before.

05:41.427 --> 05:44.310
Don't need to skip around and go back to the front.

05:44.851 --> 05:45.591
Why is that?

05:47.173 --> 06:04.050
Because if you devote your life to the pursuit of security and comfort and ease and you succeed, gain the whole world, zero, it's worth zero because you're going to lose your soul.

06:05.346 --> 06:08.070
argument number two.

06:08.090 --> 06:08.631
Why is that?

06:09.712 --> 06:13.517
Why is it that if you gain the whole world, you're going to lose your soul.

06:13.818 --> 06:15.741
You succeeded and you totally failed.

06:18.124 --> 06:21.529
Listen politicians and rich people in the news.

06:24.252 --> 06:24.933
Why is that?

06:26.516 --> 06:31.122
Because no matter how much you gain, the soul isn't for sale.

06:34.146 --> 06:35.928
No dealing on the last day.

06:36.929 --> 06:39.412
No negotiating on the last day.

06:39.472 --> 06:40.553
Bring your billions.

06:42.615 --> 06:44.177
Bring your shale collection.

06:49.182 --> 06:49.742
Why is that?

06:51.564 --> 06:52.485
That's argument number three.

06:52.505 --> 06:53.166
Now, why is that?

06:53.747 --> 06:54.808
This is what we're going to linger on.

06:54.848 --> 06:56.329
Number four, why is that?

06:56.690 --> 06:58.271
No negotiating on the last day.

06:58.491 --> 07:00.914
No deals at the judgment day.

07:04.386 --> 07:14.161
Because whoever is ashamed of me, and in my words, in this adult or since sinful generation, I'm going to be ashamed of him.

07:14.742 --> 07:21.712
Jesus says, I'm going to be ashamed of him when I come in the glory of my father and the holy angels.

07:23.014 --> 07:25.298
And I want to know what does that mean?

07:27.221 --> 07:28.683
That just took me a few weeks ago.

07:28.903 --> 07:30.866
Jesus is going to be ashamed.

07:33.314 --> 07:35.177
What will that be like for Jesus?

07:39.462 --> 07:40.864
Shame is a painful thing.

07:42.707 --> 07:43.768
Everybody's tasted it.

07:44.269 --> 07:45.351
You were in the fourth grade.

07:46.132 --> 07:48.535
I won't say what happened, but it was horrible.

07:48.595 --> 07:52.821
Everybody's tasted this.

07:55.024 --> 07:56.826
Another word for it is humiliation.

07:59.831 --> 08:02.354
Will Jesus be humiliated on the last day?

08:07.490 --> 08:12.997
When he says, the Son of Man will be ashamed of those who were ashamed of him.

08:13.037 --> 08:16.461
Does it mean the Son of Man is going to be humiliated?

08:18.443 --> 08:18.684
No.

08:20.286 --> 08:21.728
No, it doesn't mean that.

08:22.969 --> 08:24.731
He's never going to be humiliated.

08:25.712 --> 08:29.057
He's never going to hear anybody say with any truth.

08:29.117 --> 08:36.786
That was stupid, you idiot.

08:36.898 --> 08:38.139
He spies the shame.

08:38.159 --> 08:44.887
He endured the cross despising the shame.

08:48.591 --> 08:55.778
Well, what then does it mean that the Son of Man will be ashamed of those who were ashamed of Him?

08:55.838 --> 09:00.664
This is what we do.

09:04.428 --> 09:06.610
It means the same thing, doesn't it?

09:07.842 --> 09:13.910
as what those people who were ashamed of him experienced.

09:13.930 --> 09:16.854
The same way that they were ashamed of him, he'll be ashamed of them.

09:18.896 --> 09:20.078
How were they ashamed of him?

09:23.442 --> 09:35.378
The people that Jesus will be ashamed of in this text are not people who were shamed and humiliated because they stood for Jesus.

09:38.306 --> 09:47.319
He's not going to be ashamed of them, not the people who were shamed and humiliated because they stood for Jesus.

09:49.062 --> 10:02.482
No, the people he's going to be ashamed of are the people who sought to save their lives, save their wealth, save their ego, save their reputation by avoiding shame.

10:07.906 --> 10:12.111
So they didn't stand up for Jesus because they were afraid of being ashamed.

10:13.512 --> 10:15.354
They ran away from shame.

10:21.401 --> 10:37.458
In other words, to be ashamed of Jesus means to be so fearful of being shamed for Jesus that you won't stand up for Jesus in order to avoid being shamed for Jesus.

10:39.874 --> 10:53.016
Remember the apostles in Acts 541, they came out of the Sanhedrin and they rejoiced that they had been counted worthy to be shamed for the name.

11:00.188 --> 11:04.114
They were shamed, but they were not ashamed.

11:09.058 --> 11:21.113
These people here in this text, in Mark 8, that Jesus is going to be ashamed of, they would not embrace the shame, the way the apostles did.

11:21.153 --> 11:30.185
They didn't embrace it, they didn't rejoice in it, they shunned it, they were afraid of it, and they kept their mouths shut instead of speaking up for Jesus.

11:34.430 --> 11:37.714
Now we're in a position to know what it means for Jesus to be ashamed.

11:43.426 --> 11:57.666
Just as these faithless ones would have been humiliated if they stood up for Jesus in an adulterous and sinful generation, they chose not to stand up for Jesus to avoid being shamed.

11:58.567 --> 12:05.556
And so Jesus on the last day will avoid being shamed by not standing up for them.

12:10.523 --> 12:12.626
They avoided humiliation

12:12.930 --> 12:23.204
By not acknowledging Jesus, he will avoid humiliation before his father and the angels by not acknowledging them.

12:23.264 --> 12:28.351
Everyone who acknowledges me before men, I will acknowledge before my father.

12:28.631 --> 12:32.817
Everyone who denies me before men, I will deny before my father, Matthew 10, 32.

12:35.640 --> 12:39.245
They refuse to advocate for Jesus, to avoid shame.

12:39.305 --> 12:42.770
He will refuse to advocate for them, to avoid shame.

12:45.282 --> 12:51.490
They saved face with fools by distancing themselves from the wise.

12:53.172 --> 13:00.000
And Jesus will save face with the wise by distancing himself from fools.

13:02.923 --> 13:14.898
Or to just simply read the text again, whoever is ashamed of me and of my words, in this adulterous and sinful generation, of him will the son of man be ashamed when he comes in with his

13:15.170 --> 13:17.072
in the power of his father and with his holy angels.

13:19.935 --> 13:25.141
Okay, so graduates, bringing this now to a point for you.

13:26.322 --> 13:28.345
I ask a question.

13:28.425 --> 13:30.447
That's what we do here.

13:30.487 --> 13:34.251
We ask questions and then we try to answer them and that's how we grow.

13:34.511 --> 13:36.373
Asking questions is the key to understanding.

13:36.654 --> 13:37.555
So here's my question.

13:40.798 --> 13:44.082
Is what we have just seen on the judgment day

13:45.058 --> 13:48.122
Salvation by grace through faith.

13:52.308 --> 13:58.898
Or is it an earned salvation through works?

14:02.262 --> 14:03.504
Go home to your assignment.

14:05.907 --> 14:07.490
Nope.

14:07.510 --> 14:08.972
I did that for you.

14:10.654 --> 14:13.458
To answer that question, oppose another one.

14:13.538 --> 14:17.963
That's what Jesus did in this text, question, rhetorical question after rhetorical question.

14:17.983 --> 14:20.206
With no answers, you're supposed to give the answer.

14:22.288 --> 14:24.691
Here's my second illuminating question.

14:26.993 --> 14:33.841
Do you earn the love Christ has for you by treasuring it?

14:38.166 --> 14:39.788
No, you do not.

14:41.229 --> 14:41.970
You were dead.

14:43.618 --> 14:48.965
You were dead when His great love made you alive.

14:50.347 --> 14:54.392
By grace you have been saved through faith is not your own doing.

14:54.412 --> 14:55.453
This is a gift of God.

14:59.759 --> 15:08.069
When Christ pours His love out on you and you treasure it more than the affirmation of an adulterous generation, you've earned anything.

15:08.130 --> 15:11.634
It's all been done.

15:17.186 --> 15:35.126
If you're ashamed of Christ and His words, if you value the approval of an adulterous and sinful generation over Christ, you're not failing to earn the love of Christ.

15:35.406 --> 15:37.489
You're failing to see it.

15:42.935 --> 15:45.778
We've spent four years laboring with you.

15:46.850 --> 16:01.524
to learn how to see and see through to value, to embrace, to treasure the infinite worth and beauty and greatness of the love of God in Christ.

16:03.286 --> 16:06.969
This is what you're going to do for the rest of your life, whatever your vocation.

16:07.029 --> 16:08.511
This is what you're going to do.

16:08.551 --> 16:16.338
If you turn away from the treasure of Christ,

16:16.962 --> 16:25.013
and value the approval of the world, the adulterous and sinful generation.

16:25.033 --> 16:42.977
If you turn away from the treasure of Christ and treasure the approval of an adulterous generation, that is, if you're ashamed of Christ, this is not a failure to earn the love of Christ.

16:43.658 --> 16:46.322
This is a failure to see the love of Christ.

16:50.434 --> 17:02.509
These four years have been a beginning, a launching into a lifelong learning to see and to see through.

17:02.549 --> 17:06.194
To see Jesus, see Jesus.

17:06.554 --> 17:07.776
He's really alive.

17:07.816 --> 17:10.099
He's in this room, folks.

17:10.960 --> 17:11.641
He's alive.

17:12.202 --> 17:12.562
He's here.

17:19.234 --> 17:37.339
a lifelong learning to see, see through, to see Jesus as wiser, stronger, more valuable, more precious, more desirable, more satisfying, more satisfying than the approval of all the world.

17:39.922 --> 17:48.434
So keep on seeing the Word and keep on seeing through to reality.

17:50.594 --> 17:54.959
you will never be ashamed.

17:54.979 --> 18:18.866
Oh, Father, for the graduates and everybody in this room, wean us off the pleasure of being approved by adulterers and centers, and addict us

18:20.898 --> 18:25.092
to the sweetness of Christ.

18:28.103 --> 18:29.106
I ask in His name.

